  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "According to the [JSON RPC spec](https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API) `eth_signTransaction` uses a gas default. However, when  trying to sign a transaction with the gas field missing, geth reports ` { code: -32000, message: \"gas not specified\" }`.\r\n\r\nThis does not happen when e.g. using the same transaction with the `eth_sendTransaction` procedure.\r\n\r\nI am not sure if this is intended behavior or a bug. This behavior was observed using geth in `--dev` mode.",
